<br>
One other thing that i hate are LAZY WIZARDS!<br>
We are in a group hunting giants. we got a mage (me) a wizzy a monk a warrior and a cleric.  Whenever the monk pulls i see the mage get up and cast one friggin spell.  While the monk and warrior are getting worked i'm nuking my but off and the Giant decides he wants to turn me into a punching bag what do i see the wizzy MEDDING! we finally kill him I'm almost dead (thank goodness for the the phantom chain)and my group wants to pull another.  I SAY HELL NO I'M OOM! then the friggin group says all at once why are you OOM? at these words i have left many groups, and a few more things i hate necromancers who try to be nukers and clerics who try to be warriors KNOW YOUR ROLE PEOPLE!<br>
MAGE POWER! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Raminy</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(1/14/01 5:17:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   oops</span><hr size=1> err the wizzy get up and cast one friggin spell (sorry was to angry to type correctly) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uuinael.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uinael</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#333333>(1/15/01 7:11:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerrants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eagleeyeweb.com/eq/uinface.gif width=89 height=200></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: oops</span><hr size=1>  imo mages should never be out of mana.. especially with a wiz in group. The only time is when you are fighting for your life (ie bad pulls). Burn all your mana to finish off the mobs quick. <br>
<br>
 If the giants were aggro'ing you, you were probably overnuking. Let the tanks bring the mob to 50-60% life before casting your first nuke. Then sit, let tanks do more damage and throw some more nukes in to finish it off if you need to. <br>
<br>
 As far as mage/necro comparison.. I don't think there is one. At the lower lvls it was a bit closer, but higher lvls it is comparing apples and oranges. After lvl 50 necros do not have pets anymore, they have DoTs that they control. See how long a necro pet lasts tanking lvl 50 mobs.. they have so few HPs it is kind of sad. <br>
<br>
 Everyone complains about necro DoT's too saying how powerful they are.. but just think about how much damage a lvl 56 mage dishes out in a group with a warrior. I counted one fight a warrior got hit 35 times against a non slowed frog in OS.. here is some damage.. <br>
<br>
Damage Shield - 33 * 35 = 1155<br>
Pet - guessing 3-5k damage<br>
Nukes - 700-4000 depending on how much you nuke<br>
<br>
You can probably max 7k damage on a froggie in OS w/o getting aggro'd and beaten to death if you do it right. Lets see a necro say the same thing.  I never added up necro damage, but I doubt they come close. <br>
<br>
<br>
